titles, text, number of verses and their sequence, page-layout, context) and the means of controlling them in the manuscripts of the poems are identified and detailed descriptions of the copies are given.The monograph also includes a presentation of some major traits of the cultural background to the study of Arabic didactic poetry and of its dissemination in which memorization has played a crucial role. The intended readers, editors and other users of manuscripts, are helped to acquaint themselves with the methods employed in the manuscripts to control variation and they are given an overview of the large spectrum of Arabic didactic poetry and of its place in the traditional culture of learning in Islamicate societies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aArabic poetryy1258-1800xHistory and criticismxCriticism, Textual. 0aArabic poetryy750-1258xHistory and criticismxCriticism, Textual. 0aDidactic poetry, ArabicxHistory and criticism. 0aManuscripts, ArabiczIslamic Empire. 0aTransmission of textszIslamic Empire. 4aLehrdichtung. 4aMündliche Überlieferung. 4aSchriftliche Überlieferung. 4aVarianz. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aVariance.  adidactic poetry.  aorality and writing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z97831107010050 cEPUBz97831104600010 cprintz978311045869540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110